      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "QUEEN KIZEN NZ (3) looks close to a win after string of placings. Came from this barrier for second at Melton two starts back then had a 20m handicap at her latest appearance at Maryborough but worked to the front and then stuck on, beaten 3.7 metres into third. Draws for a nice run and could break through. ALDEBARAN SUSANNE (8) has switched yards since galloping out when resuming at Menangle. No harm in drawing here with the sprint lane to rely upon. Has the ability if she gets it right. OFF YOUR FACESKI (4) backs up off a sixth at Melton on Saturday. Led from only spot lower than this when scoring easily at Geelong prior. Contender. MAJESTIC TOOTH (1) owns a good record at this circuit and should get her chance from the ace draw.",
